 October, he sat on the judging panel for 1 Minute to Save the World, a competition for short films about climate change. (And yes, last summer, he was a judge on <em>India&#39;s Got Talent</em>.) </p><p>His forthcoming film <em>Paani</em> &ndash; the hindi word for water &ndash; explores mumbai&#39;s shrinking supply of water and its distribution underworld. equally at home in hollywood and Bollywood, he&#39;s also a comics mogul; in 2006 he co-founded Virgin Comics as a venue for turning Indian and Hindu myths into pop-culture icons. For the company, now reorganized as Liquid Comics, he cocreated the series <em>Ramayan 3392 A.D.</em>, based on the Ramayana. His newest Liquid series: <em>Devi</em>.</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Shekhar Kapur","tags":["creativity","entertainment","film","india"],"title":"We are the stories we tell ourselves","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":757333}]}
